==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cauliflower
<hw>Cau"li*flow`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>choufleur</ets>, modified by E. <ets>Cole</ets>. L.
<ets>caulis</ets>, and by E. <ets>flower</ets>; F. <ets>chou</ets>
cabbage is fr. L. <ets>caulis</ets> stalk, cabbage, and <ets>fleur</ets>
flower is fr. L. <ets>flos</ets> flower. See <er>Cole</er>, and
<er>Flower</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An annual
variety of <spn>Brassica oleracea</spn>, or cabbage, of which the
cluster of young flower stalks and buds is eaten as a
vegetable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The edible head or ⟦ldquo⟧curd⟦rdquo⟧ of a
cauliflower plant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cauliform</ent>⟦br⟧
